GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 616
Committee Substitute Favorable 4/29/25
Short Title: Megasites/Selectsites Program Revisions. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
April 1, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE MEGASITES AND SELECTSITES READINESS PROGRAMS.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1.(a) Section 11.11 of S.L. 2022-74, as amended by Section 11.11 of S.L.
5 2023-134, reads as rewritten:
6 "SECTION 11.11.(a) Purpose. – It is in the best economic and developmental interests of
7 the State to support the development of megasites to ensure the State's ongoing competitiveness
8 for major manufacturing opportunities, including, but not limited to, the aerospace, automotive,
9 clean energy, food processing, semiconductor, and life science industries. The purpose of this
10 section is to establish a competitive grant program serving to do the following:
11 (1) Identify and evaluate up to seven megasites for preferred development and
12 marketing.
13 (2) Assist local governments or a partnership of local governments in the
14 acquisition of a newly identified or existing megasite.
15 (3) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to analyze,
16 plan, install, or upgrade public infrastructure, including publicly owned water,
17 gas, and sewer systems, transportation infrastructure, and the electrical utility
18 lines electric infrastructure necessary to meet the needs of prospective
19 employers for megasites.
20 (4) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to fund
21 on-site preparation, including clearing, grading, or other related expenses for
22 megasites.
23 (4a) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments in
24 conducting due diligence, including, but not limited to, the following: site
25 characteristics, preliminary engineering reports for water and wastewater
26 provision to the site, assessments related to road and highway infrastructure
27 to serve the site, and other assessments as needed.
28 (5) Facilitate coordination between the economic development entities, the North
29 Carolina Department of Environmental Quality, and the North Carolina
30 Department of Transportation to expedite needs related to timely site
31 development.
32 …
33 "SECTION 11.11.(c) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
34 …
35 (4) Government partnership. – Either (i) a North Carolina nonprofit entity that is
36 tax exempt under section 501(c)(3) or 501(c)(12) of the Internal Revenue
*H616-v-2*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Code in partnership with one or more local governments or (ii) a group of
2 local governments.
3 …
4 "SECTION 11.11.(d) Allocation. – EDPNC shall allocate monies in the Fund on the
5 following basis:
6 …
7 (2) All other funds appropriated to the Fund for local government grants for the
8 acquisition of megasites determined pursuant to subdivision (1) of this
9 subsection. purposes described in subsection (a) of this section. A grant for
10 the acquisition of a megasite is limited to eighty-five percent (85%) of the
11 lesser of the property's purchase price or tax value. The percentage actually
12 provided in the grant shall be determined by EDPNC based on total
13 development needs for the megasite, prior investment in the megasite by one
14 or more local governments, the ability of one or more local governments to
15 invest in the megasite, and the ability and level of participation promised by
16 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
17 be granted for, and used to acquire, a megasite for which (i) one or more local
18 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
19 diligence must be complete, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
20 title searches, State Historic Preservation Office reviews, and wetlands
21 delineation.
22 …
23 "SECTION 11.11.(f) Agreements Required. – Monies may be disbursed from the Fund
24 previously appropriated for the Megasite Readiness Program shall be transferred in full to
25 EDPNC when this act becomes law. Funds subsequently appropriated for the Program shall be
26 transferred in full to EDPNC once such an act becomes law. EDPNC may use funds only in
27 accordance with agreements that are (i) entered into between EDPNC and a local government or
28 a government partnership and (ii) approved by the Economic Investment Committee established
29 pursuant to G.S. 143B-437.54. The agreement must include all of the performance criteria,
30 remedies, and other safeguards required to secure the assistance provided to ready the megasite
31 for a major employer and must require EDPNC to recapture a proportionate amount of assistance
32 provided under this section for failure by a local government or government partnership to meet
33 and maintain the megasite for availability for the purposes for which the assistance was provided.
34 …."
35 SECTION 1.(b) Section 11.12 of S.L. 2023-134 reads as rewritten:
36 "SECTION 11.12.(a) Funds appropriated by Section 11.4 11.4(d)(1) of S.L. 2022-74 to the
37 Department of Commerce (Department) and allocated to the nonprofit corporation with which
38 the Department contracts pursuant to G.S. 143B-431.01(b) that remain unspent as of June 30,
39 2023, April 1, 2025, shall be transferred to the North Carolina Selectsite Fund established in
40 subsection (c) of this section to be used for purposes consistent with subdivision (e)(1) of this
41 section. Of the funds appropriated from the Economic Development Project Reserve established
42 in Section 2.2 of this act to the Department to be allocated to the nonprofit corporation with which
43 the Department contracts pursuant to G.S. 143B-431.01(b), the sum of ten million dollars
44 ($10,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2024-2025 fiscal year shall be used to support local
45 governments or a partnership of local governments in conducting due diligence as described in
46 subdivision for the purposes described in subdivisions (b)(2), (b)(3), (b)(4), and (b)(5) of this
47 section.
48 "SECTION 11.12.(b) Purpose. – It is in the best economic and developmental interests of
49 the State to support the development of selectsites to ensure the State's ongoing competitiveness
50 for major manufacturing opportunities, including, but not limited to, the aerospace, automotive,
