1 clean energy, food processing, semiconductor, and life science industries. The purpose of this
2 section is to establish a competitive grant program serving to do the following:
3 (1) Identify and evaluate up to 15 20 selectsites of less than 1,000 acres for
4 preferred development and marketing.
5 (2) Assist local governments or a partnership of local governments in the
6 acquisition of a newly identified or existing selectsite.
7 (3) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to analyze,
8 plan, install, or upgrade public infrastructure, including publicly owned water,
9 gas, and sewer systems; transportation infrastructure; and the electrical utility
10 lines electric infrastructure necessary to meet the needs of prospective
11 employers for selectsites.
12 (4) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to fund
13 on-site preparation, including clearing, grading, or other related expenses for
14 selectsites.
15 (5) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments in
16 conducting due diligence, including, but not limited to, the following: site
17 characteristics, preliminary engineering reports for water and wastewater
18 provision to the site, assessments related to road and highway infrastructure
19 to serve the site, and other assessments as needed.
20 (6) Facilitate coordination between the economic development entities and the
21 North Carolina Department of Environmental Quality and the North Carolina
22 Department of Transportation to expedite needs related to timely site
23 development.
24 …
25 "SECTION 11.12.(e) Allocation. – EDPNC shall allocate monies in the Fund on the
26 following basis:
27 (1) Unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
28 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
29 process to produce a report identifying and evaluating 15 selectsites for
30 preferred development and marketing, of which seven must be less than 500
31 acres and of which an additional two must be less than 100 acres. Further
32 unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
33 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
34 process to produce a supplemental report identifying and evaluating up to five,
35 and no less than three, additional selectsites from the initial disaster declared
36 counties resulting from Tropical Storm Helene.
37 (2) Funds appropriated to the Fund for local government grants shall be allocated
38 for the purposes outlined in subdivisions (b)(2), (b)(3), (b)(4), and (b)(5) of
39 this section for selectsites determined pursuant to subdivision (1) of this
40 subsection. EDPNC shall prioritize local government grants that have the
41 greatest potential to reduce the time for site readiness and reduce the risk of
42 unforeseen conditions that could affect the site viability for advanced
43 manufacturing projects. EDPNC shall base the grant amount on total
44 development needs for the selectsite, prior investment in the selectsite by one
45 or more local governments, the ability of one or more local governments to
46 invest in the selectsite, and the ability and level of participation promised by
47 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
48 be granted for, and used to acquire, a selectsite for which (i) one or more local
49 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
50 diligence has been completed, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
